# Force LF newlines on checkout for all text the runtime reads byte-for-byte.
#
# v8.15 introduced src/content/skills/*.md, which the compiled module loads
# via fs.readFileSync. Windows' default `core.autocrlf=true` checks `.md`
# files out with CRLF, which breaks `body.startsWith("---\n")` and any other
# downstream string comparison that assumes LF-only line endings.
#
# We also normalize CRLF in the loader as defence-in-depth, but pinning the
# on-disk encoding here keeps `git diff` clean and makes the file the same
# bytes on every contributor's machine.

* text=auto eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.ts text eol=lf
*.tsx text eol=lf
*.js text eol=lf
*.mjs text eol=lf
*.cjs text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
*.mdc text eol=lf
